main event: Observation of a bright white object in the sky that was brighter than first magnitude stars, noted for its unusual maneuvers and high altitude.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 5 minutes., The position was at 34 degrees 42 minutes North and 163 degrees 42 minutes East., The elevation of the object was approximately 50 degrees., The object was heading south and was visible to the naked eye., The sky was clear during the observation.
